sec.p:
Data analysis was performed using SPSS 26.0 software. Measurement data are presented as improvement degree and mean ± standard deviation. Comparisons before and after treatment were conducted using paired t‐tests and Wilcoxon signed‐rank tests. p < 0.05 was considered statistically significant. To further quantify the magnitude of the treatment effect, within‐subject effect sizes (Cohen's d

z
) were calculated for the primary ultrasound outcomes (SLEB width and dermal thickness).
